		{"id":"ad34448eba7d4372","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Matter Web 2.png","x":-1826,"y":-2560,"width":793,"height":495},
		{"id":"0ed0a3262c7fe3a4","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621124519.png","x":-700,"y":-3220,"width":785,"height":490},
		{"id":"399c91460d174e9c","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621124526.png","x":-1826,"y":-3255,"width":889,"height":555},
		{"id":"d7ec5a71c4533f89","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Mobbin Web Screen Mobbin UI UX design inspiration for mobile web.mp4","x":-1780,"y":-3900,"width":880,"height":550},
		{"id":"680a95e74c79a60e","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621144220.png","x":-3732,"y":-2427,"width":835,"height":519},
		{"id":"4bdd82d352b10284","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Runway Web 2.png","x":-4739,"y":-2427,"width":916,"height":575},
		{"id":"fa416e0690b61b05","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621122859.png","x":-3785,"y":-3052,"width":905,"height":564},
		{"id":"7be272a1be12e350","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621143748.png","x":-3792,"y":-3780,"width":860,"height":535},
		{
			"id":"f79e09e0077a9331",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# INSPO",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2440,
			"y":-1140,
			"width":260,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"a2769915cb2fd582",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Login n Sign-Up Screen",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-3148,
			"y":-1158,
			"width":440,
			"height":100
		},
		{
			"id":"59c17243560f6852",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"#  Good Signup Pages Reduce Future Anxiety\n\nLook at wording.\n\nBad wording:\n\n```\nCreate account\n```\n\nGood wording:\n\n```\nStart free trialContinueJoin cohortExplore\n```\n\nThe subtle message:\n\n```\nYou aren't marrying us.You're trying us.\n```\n\nDesigners reduce future commitment fear.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4880,
			"y":-1280,
			"width":712,
			"height":520
		},
		{
			"id":"56897bddd0185c3f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==Signup Screens Are Actually Risk Screens==\n\nThe user's hidden questions:\n\n```\nWill this waste my time?Will they spam me?Will I regret this?Will this be useful?Can I leave later?\n```\n\nThe best signup pages answer those questions without explicitly saying them",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-3725,
			"y":-102,
			"width":420,
			"height":460
		},
		{
			"id":"c4edcc510d2a51d1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==Labels Above Fields Are Disappearing==\n\n==Many modern forms rely heavily on placeholders.==\n\nThis isn't always better UX.\n\nBut it reveals something:\n\nDesigners are trying to reduce visual density.\n\nThey're trading explicitness for simplicity.\n\nVeterans know:\n\n```\nLow frictionvsHigh clarity\n```\n\nis a constant tradeoff.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2740,
			"y":160,
			"width":520,
			"height":472
		},
		{
			"id":"3e6e48cdb5d1d543",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==The Screen Is Split Into Two Brains==\n\nAll three examples use:\n\n```\nLeft Side  = Emotional Brain\nRight Side = Rational Brain\n```\n\nor vice versa.\n\nThe form exists for the rational brain.\n\nThe marketing panel exists for the emotional brain.\n\n---\n\nTraditional signup:\n\n```\n[ Form ]\n```\n\nSplit-screen signup:\n\n```\n[ Why this matters ] [ Do the thing ]\n```\n\nHuge difference.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-5171,
			"y":-4760,
			"width":500,
			"height":680
		},
		{
			"id":"e564b6ef4cba61ff",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# They're Fighting Form Blindness\n\nPeople have seen signup forms 10,000 times.\n\nTheir brain automatically categorizes:\n\n```\nName\nEmail\nPassword\n```\n\nas administrative work.\n\nThe marketing panel interrupts that autopilot.\n\nIt reminds the user:\n\n```\nThis is not paperwork.\nThis is access.\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-5457,
			"y":-666,
			"width":520,
			"height":564
		},
		{
			"id":"50bab79fa0cdc2ee",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Left Panel Is A Psychological Preview\n\nRemote does this particularly well.\n\nNotice the mini UI mockups.\n\nThose aren't screenshots.\n\nThey're future memories.\n\nThe page is showing:\n\n```\nAfter signup...this is what life looks like.\n```\n\nThe brain loves previews.\n\nUncertainty drops.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4281,
			"y":-4760,
			"width":549,
			"height":480
		},
		{
			"id":"1fa8a9ecc2a48204",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"#  ==Selling reduced complexity== \n\"All in one\" approach\n\nEnterprise Signup Has Different Anxiety\n\nConsumer signup anxiety:\n\n```\nWill this be useful?\n```\n\nEnterprise signup anxiety:\n\n```\nWill this create work?\n```\n\nThat's why these pages emphasize:\n\n```\nsimpl\neeasy\nglobal\nfast\nall-in-one\n```\n\nThey're selling reduced complexity.\n\nNot excitement.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4440,
			"y":260,
			"width":460,
			"height":600
		},
		{
			"id":"f9a8caffe0ada60d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Most Pages Have One Visual Gravity Center\n\nYour eyes are pulled somewhere.\n\nUsually:\n\n```\nheadlineformillustration\n```\n\nNot all three equally.\n\nOne dominates.\n\nThe others support.\n\nGood pages have hierarchy.\n\nBad pages have competition.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-3530,
			"y":-4760,
			"width":432,
			"height":560
		},
		{"id":"81d0a6dd3c63512f","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260620115306.png","x":-1429,"y":-416,"width":892,"height":544},
		{
			"id":"27505d17a56f8b42",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Visual Weight Distribution\n\nNotice something most people never consciously notice.\n\nThe marketing side is visually heavier.\n\nThe form side is visually lighter.\n\nExample:\n\n```\nDark panelIllustrationsLarge graphics→Simple white form\n```\n\nWhy?\n\nBecause attention should first land on:\n\n```\nvalue\n```\n\nand only then on:\n\n```\neffort\n```\n\nThe sequence matters.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-1680,
			"y":-1158,
			"width":560,
			"height":620
		},
		{
			"id":"dbcad78aa53aa8fd",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Marketing Side Is Not Selling Features\n\nLook closely.\n\nAlmost none of the panels are feature-heavy.\n\nThey're outcome-heavy.\n\nNot:\n\n```\nPayroll\nCompliance\nContracts\n```\n\nBut:\n\n```\nHire internationally\n```\n\n---\n\nNot:\n\n```\nTeam management dashboard\n```\n\nBut:\n\n```\nManage global teams\n```\n\nThe signup screen sells transformation.\n\nNot capability.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-5560,
			"y":260,
			"width":540,
			"height":880
		},
		{
			"id":"c454611c3e604983",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## These Animations Are Not Explaining\n\nThey're Signaling.\n\nBig distinction.\n\nA founder thinks:\n\n> I need users to understand everything.\n\nVeteran designer thinks:\n\n> I need users to believe something valuable exists behind this door.\n\nThe animation isn't teaching.\n\nIt's creating confidence.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2000,
			"y":-5020,
			"width":440,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"77bd5c0b0275faec",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Motion Creates Momentum Before Signup\n\nPeople underestimate this.\n\nA static page feels:\n\n```\nstopped\n```\n\nA moving page feels:\n\n```\nalready in progress\n```\n\nHumans naturally want to join moving things.\n\nThis is why:\n\n```\ncrowds attract crowdsbusy restaurants attract peopleactive communities attract members\n```\n\nMotion creates the feeling:\n\n```\nsomething is happening here\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-120,
			"y":-5020,
			"width":260,
			"height":780
		},
		{
			"id":"5f8c05b87ba59937",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## The User Has No Mental Model Yet\n\nThis is especially important for SideQuestHQ.\n\nFor known products:\n\n```\nSlackDiscordLinkedIn\n```\n\npeople already know what happens after signup.\n\nFor new categories:\n\n```\nMobbinSideQuestHQNovel SaaS\n```\n\nthey don't.\n\nThe biggest anxiety becomes:\n\n> What happens after I create this account?\n\nAnimation answers that before the question fully forms.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-686,
			"y":-5180,
			"width":380,
			"height":740
		},
		{
			"id":"fbf4ab9de7235c47",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Motion Creates Perceived Product Depth\n\nThis is subtle.\n\nSuppose two products are identical.\n\nProduct A:\n\n```\nstatic screenshot\n```\n\nProduct B:\n\n```\nmoving ecosystem preview\n```\n\nPeople consistently perceive Product B as:\n\n```\nlargermore sophisticatedmore valuable\n```\n\nEven when functionality is identical.\n\nWhy?\n\nBecause movement implies systems.\n\nStatic implies pages.\n\nMotion implies an engine.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-1520,
			"y":-5020,
			"width":520,
			"height":667
		},
		{
			"id":"47b640cd8abb0ad5",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Gifting Platform\n\nBackground shows:\n\n```\nbeautiful products\n```\n\nNarrative:\n\n```\ndiscover gifts\n```\n\n---\n\n### ElevenLabs\n\nBackground shows:\n\n```\nvoice cards\ngenerated outputs\n```\n\nNarrative:\n\n```\ncreate voices\n```\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":400,
			"y":-2362,
			"width":400,
			"height":602
		},
		{
			"id":"66410c35ee29281b",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Background Is Doing Narrative Work\n\nLet's classify them.\n\n### Matter\n\nBackground shows:\n\n```\ncommunity activity\n```\n\nNarrative:\n\n```\njoin the conversation\n```\n\n---\n\n### Claude\n\nBackground shows:\n\n```\nworkspace\nartifacts\ncreation\n```\n\nNarrative:\n\n```\nbuild things\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2660,
			"y":-2620,
			"width":660,
			"height":787
		},
		{
			"id":"88e133fe4aa27013",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## The Dating App Example Uses a Different Strategy\n\nNotice it doesn't show features.\n\nIt shows:\n\n```\npeople\nprofiles\nactivity\nmatches\n```\n\nWhy?\n\nBecause dating products aren't selling software.\n\nThey're selling outcomes.\n\nThe outcome is:\n\n```\nmeeting someone\n```\n\nnot\n\n```\nusing the app\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":340,
			"y":-4060,
			"width":414,
			"height":737
		},
		{"id":"a45ea6a0b36d8424","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621143915.png","x":-800,"y":-3880,"width":927,"height":580},
		{
			"id":"74e60c9523754cd0",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The User Is Already Mentally Using The Product\n\nClaude is the strongest example.\n\nThe workspace preview lets me imagine:\n\n```\nmy projectmy documentmy workflow\n```\n\nbefore I've even typed my email.\n\nThat is essentially free product adoption happening before signup.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-900,
			"y":-1220,
			"width":400,
			"height":420
		},
		{
			"id":"1d141b9562d33bac",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==The highest-leverage insight for SideQuestHQ==\n\nA veteran UX designer would likely conclude:\n\n**The first signup screen should not start with account creation.**\n\nIt should start with identity and intent.\n\nNot:\n\n```\nEmailPasswordCreate account\n```\n\nBut:\n\n```\nWhat do you want to finish learning?\n```\n\nBecause your product promise is not:\n\n> Create an account.\n\nYour product promise is:\n\n> Continue the thing you keep postponing.\n\nThe moment a user types:\n\n```\nMachine Learning Playlist\nGerman\nPsychology\nSystem Design\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2086,
			"y":180,
			"width":520,
			"height":760
		},
		{
			"id":"2f00469f6c3efde7",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# What A Senior Product Designer Would Notice For SideQuestHQ\n\nThese examples reveal something important:\n\n**SideQuestHQ should not show learning paths on the signup screen.**\n\nThat's the equivalent of showing database tables.\n\nIt's internal structure.\n\nNot desire.\n\nMost founders would showcase:\n\n```\ncohort cardsprogress barslearning graphadaptive scheduler\n```\n\nThose are mechanisms.\n\nNot outcomes.\n\n---\n\nThe real emotional outcome in SideQuestHQ is:\n\n```\nI finally finished something.\n```\n\nEverything in your positioning points toward that.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-2426,
			"y":-720,
			"width":680,
			"height":720
		},
		{"id":"23ea5071d764f1be","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621123411.png","x":2820,"y":-3608,"width":960,"height":600},
		{"id":"a4c3eecff8d7d3a2","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Cosmos Web 8.png","x":1739,"y":-3584,"width":1000,"height":623},
		{
			"id":"db5894a3f112dac2",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# White Space Is Doing Psychological Work\n\nHuge empty regions exist.\n\nNot because designers had nothing to add.\n\nBecause signup is a single-task screen.\n\nEvery extra element creates:\n\n```\ndecision branchesattention forkscognitive load\n```\n\nVeterans aggressively remove options.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2470,
			"y":-4303,
			"width":530,
			"height":500
		},
		{"id":"28f1a61bac47830e","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621143425.png","x":3780,"y":-2588,"width":999,"height":625},
		{"id":"42d68b22c3f35e2b","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621144431.png","x":3780,"y":-1791,"width":999,"height":622},
		{"id":"0117b6495998caee","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Linear Web 3.png","x":1600,"y":-2589,"width":1000,"height":623},
		{"id":"7621ef40055a8b18","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621123122.png","x":1600,"y":-1793,"width":999,"height":624},
		{"id":"b0f9528d586c83e2","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621124417.png","x":2679,"y":-2639,"width":1000,"height":626},
		{"id":"b7667c0df10e3c87","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260621144117.png","x":2776,"y":-1793,"width":903,"height":566},
		{
			"id":"fa841de77acadaa5",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Pattern 1  Progressive Commitment\n\nNotice how the simplest page is:\n\n- logo\n- email field\n- continue\n\nNo password.  \nNo name.  \nNo phone.\n\nThis isn't laziness.\n\nThis is commitment architecture.\n\nThe brain evaluates:\n\n```\n1 field = easy7 fields = work\n```\n\nEven if both ultimately require the same information.\n\nDesigners call this:\n\n**Perceived Effort Reduction**\n\nThe user mentally says:\n\n> \"Sure, I can enter an email.\"\n\nOnly after commitment begins do you ask for more.\n\n---",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1080,
			"y":-2671,
			"width":320,
			"height":780
		},
		{"id":"fc62416f002ce760","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260620115542.png","x":1100,"y":-76,"width":1481,"height":753},
		{
			"id":"e1c8eda1297ed98b",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Signup Pages Borrow Trust\n\nLook closely.\n\nPeopleGPT:\n\n- logos\n- testimonials\n- badges\n\nResume:\n\n- companies\n- statistics\n- founder quote\n\nPeerlist:\n\n- users already inside\n\nThe page is essentially saying:\n\n```\nDon't trust us.Trust everyone already using us.\n```\n\nThis is called:\n\n**Borrowed Trust**",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":5125,
			"y":-1891,
			"width":560,
			"height":720
		},
		{
			"id":"9c2ba4ab5cc0e83f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Form Density Signals Company Type\n\nCompare:\n\n### Arcade\n\nTiny form\n\n```\nEmail\nContinue\n```\n\nFeels:\n\n```\nmodern\nstartup\nlow friction\nconsumer-ish\n```\n\n---\n\n### Deel\n\nMassive form\n\n```\nFirst name\nLast name\nCompanyRole\n```\n\nFeels:\n\n```\nserious\nenterprise\nB2B\nhigh-value\n```\n\nInteresting paradox:\n\nSometimes MORE fields increase trust.\n\nBecause the user expects seriousness.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":5005,
			"y":-3451,
			"width":660,
			"height":1198
		},
		{
			"id":"aba4323ff9e61dd7",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Invisible Question\n\nEvery signup page is answering:\n\n```\nWhy should I create an account?\n```\n\nbefore asking:\n\n```\nCreate an account\n```\n\nLook carefully.\n\nEvery example has value communication:\n\n- CRM talks about growth\n- Peerlist talks about professional network\n- PeopleGPT shows social proof\n- Resume shows outcomes\n\nBecause signup is fundamentally a sales problem.\n\nNot a UI problem.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3429,
			"y":-860,
			"width":620,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"89b88bf4f54971e1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Form Width Is Intentionally Small\n\nNotice most forms are narrow.\n\nThis is not aesthetic.\n\nWide forms create:\n\n```\nlong eye travellarge visual footprinthigher perceived complexity\n```\n\nNarrow forms create:\n\n```\nquick scanningshorter eye movementsfaster completion\n```\n\nHuman brains estimate effort visually before reading.\n\nA narrow form literally feels easier.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2019,
			"y":-831,
			"width":660,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"af91739f1e999b6c",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Social Proof Is Positioned Near Decision Points\n\nNotice where proof appears.\n\nNot at the top.\n\nNot hidden.\n\nUsually:\n\n```\nnear buttonnear formnear CTA\n```\n\nReason:\n\nTrust decays.\n\nThe user needs reassurance exactly when uncertainty peaks.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":4404,
			"y":-800,
			"width":540,
			"height":600
		}
	],
	"edges":[
		{
			"id":"430ff365cc377737",
